CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper November 17, 1945, pg. 13, reads: "Boys Come Marching Home - Veterans of World Wars I and II, as well as other wars - in uniform and out - marched in the Armistice Day parade here Monday. American Legion units, Veterans of Foreign Wars, Amvets, Boy Scouts, Girl Scouts, drill clubs, floats, and brightly-colored banners made up the parade, which took more than two hours to pass. It was the first military celebration since V-E and V-J Days, and the town celebrated in its best style. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Armistice Day parade with American Legion Post 82 float reenacting the flag raising at Iwo Jima, passing by Rosenbaum's department store, Liberty Avenue, Downtown
